 Update Threat Models with New Data Inputs
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Integrate telemetry and network data into MITRE ATT&CK-based threat models
Analyze security events to identify attack patterns and threat indicators
Automate threat model updates using Python scripts
Generate actionable threat intelligence reports
Implement continuous monitoring workflows for dynamic threat modeling
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of cybersecurity and threat modeling concepts
Familiarity with MITRE ATT&CK framework
Python programming fundamentals
Linux command line experience
Knowledge of JSON data formats
